track.name: Born With A Beer In My Hand

wiki.summary: “Born With A Beer In My Hand” is an ode to Morgan Wallen’s family history of drinking and his own personal struggles with alcohol. The lyrics highlight how his upbringing and surroundings normalized alcohol consumption and how it has impacted his life, including leading to troubles with the law enforcement. Despite acknowledging the dangers of drinking, Wallen sings about how it’s still a part of his life, but he’s doing the best he can to moderate it. Read more on Last.fm.
